Privacy Policy
Thank you for choosing to use our application (hereinafter referred to as the "App"). We attach great importance to your privacy and personal information protection, so we have formulated this Privacy Policy to clarify how we collect, use, store and share your personal information. Please read the following terms carefully before using our APP and confirm that you agree that we will process your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
1. Information Collection
Device Information: In order to provide better services, we may collect device information such as your device model, operating system version, IP address, MAC address, etc. This information will help us understand the compatibility of user devices and optimize APP performance.
Usage Data: We may collect data such as the frequency, duration, and function usage of your APP to analyze user behavior and improve user experience.
Location Information (if applicable): Some functions may require your location information to provide location-based personalized services. We will clearly inform you and obtain your consent before collecting such information.
2. Information Use
Provide services: We use the collected information to provide, optimize and personalize the functions and services of the APP.
Analysis and Improvement: By analyzing the collected information, we can understand user needs and preferences and improve the design and functions of the APP.
Push notifications: Based on your interests and behaviors, we may push relevant notifications and advertisements to you. You can turn off these notifications in the APP settings.
Legal compliance: When necessary, we may provide your personal information to relevant departments in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations.
3. Information sharing
Internal sharing: We only share your personal information internally for the purpose of providing services.
Third-party services: We may share anonymous or de-identified information with third-party service providers (such as advertisers, data analysis companies, etc.) to provide better services and optimize user experience.
Legal requirements: Under the premise of complying with laws and regulations, we may provide your personal information to third parties in accordance with legal requirements or instructions from government departments.
4. Information security
We take a variety of security measures to protect your personal information, including but not limited to encryption technology, access control, security audits, etc. However, due to the complexity of the network environment, we cannot guarantee absolute security. Therefore, it is recommended that you update your password regularly, stay vigilant, and avoid personal information leakage.
5. Your rights
Access and correction: You have the right to access and correct your personal information.
Deletion: You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information, but please note that deleting certain information may affect the normal use of the APP.
Withdrawal of consent: You have the right to withdraw your consent to our processing of personal information at any time. After withdrawing your consent, we will stop processing your personal information, but it will not affect the information processing that has been carried out before.
Complaints: If you have any questions or complaints about our privacy policy, please contact us through the contact information in the APP.
6. Policy Updates
We may update this privacy policy in accordance with changes in laws and regulations or the needs of business development. The updated privacy policy will be published in the APP and notified to you in an appropriate manner. Please check the privacy policy regularly to understand our latest policies.
7. User Consent for Data Processing Related to Refund Requests
In accordance with the App Store’s refund policy, when a user initiates a refund request, our server will receive a notification (CONSUMPTION_REQUEST) from Apple. In such cases, we will provide Apple with data related to the user’s subscription to assist Apple in making a decision regarding the refund request. Please note that the data provided is strictly limited to subscription-related consumption information and does not include any personal or sensitive data. We are committed to complying with Apple’s requirements and ensuring that all data processing activities fully adhere to privacy protection laws and regulations. By using this app, you consent to the transmission of your subscription consumption data to Apple, as required for processing refund requests, in compliance with the App Store’s refund policies.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or need help with this privacy policy, please contact us via email: tool231app@gmail.com. We will respond to you as soon as possible and provide you with necessary help.
Thank you for your attention and understanding of this privacy policy. We promise to continue to work hard to provide you with safer and more convenient services.
